<br>
If you are going to run/moderate the &quot;server&quot; board at least have some consistancy. Otherwise this board will be ignored and another one will be made. This has nothing to do with FaF or any other guild for that matter.<br>
<br>
Thanks.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujaxy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaxy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mistress of the board<br>Kinda Kooky<br>Snow Bunny</span><br>  Posts: 211<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/2/01 9:15:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.soulcadre.com/chessiedoll.jpg width=64 width=178></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Locking of threads</span><hr size=1> Well, in regards to your post, thank you for expressing your concerns.  When I am working on the board it is easier for me to lock threads than when I am doing something else, if the thread needs to be locked.  It is *very* difficult to determine what needs to be locked and what doesn't.  I understand that you want consistency, but it is not as easy as that.  Being a board administrator and moderator is a difficult job in the sense that you have to use your judgement and remain neutral and try to discern what is appropriate and what is not.  I am sorry if you feel there is a problem, but we can only do so much at the right time and so much at other times to try to promote harmony and good community behavior. <p>~Chessie<br>
<a href="http://www.geocities.com/fvcircleofsisters">Circle of Sisters</link><br>
<a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie">Firiona Vie Message Board</link></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uarkitip.showPublicProfile?language=EN>arkitip</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 105<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/3/01 3:14:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Locking of threads</span><hr size=1> I don't even pretend to be a Mod, but I'll make this easy for all of them, as I KNOW the rules of most forums on the web.<br>
There have been posts &quot;flaming&quot; F&amp;F, but most of them have started as a thread that expresses one person's run ins with the guild, and which then turns into a flame war from there. That sort of post should not be locked, but the flame messages should be deleted.<br>
While that thread is a warning to players based on experiences with said entity, there is a line to be drawn. That line is when a board member makes a thread that SPECIFICALLY targets another member of the board. This invites personal attacks upon said member. THIS IS NOT ALLOWED ON NEARLY ANY BOARD. There was a guild member of yours who made such a thread proclaiming someone who visits this board to be an @ss. I have yet to see that person make such a thread himself. This type of behavior IS NOT ALLOWED on boards that have 25,000 members, let alone a board of this size.<br>
There's the difference for you, live with it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubanegrivm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Banegrivm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 291<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/3/01 4:16:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Good Points</span><hr size=1> I do however agree with the locking of a thread. Even if you do delete the thread people may still continue on with flaming therein. You are also correct that the abrupt &quot;personal attacks&quot; would not be allowed, and in many cases I have seen said individuals that take such stances likewise immediately banned also. <br>
<br>
Sadly you can have boards and what not, but the only way you will ever end certain personal attacks and flames will be to end the threads. Where it regards to posters that refuse to follow the rules and make personal attacks and what not that also state they do not care. I think the answe is simple at that point, ban them. If they state they will do as they please and do not care even after they have already had their threads locked and what not, then I think its more then clear they have no intent on following the community guidelines. <p>Banegrivm Shadowblight<br>Sovereign Lord of the 1st Fist of Light<br>www.1stfistoflight.com</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujaxy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaxy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mistress of the board<br>Kinda Kooky<br>Snow Bunny</span><br>  Posts: 213<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/3/01 4:41:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=96.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.soulcadre.com/chessiedoll.jpg width=64 width=178></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Good Points</span><hr size=1> Well, I have asked for more volunteer moderators to help with not only this forum but the board in general.  I am hoping with more moderators there'll be better board coverage.  In the moderator's forum I have asked that if there is a post that need to be looked at for board violations to please post it and the administrators will be able to look at specifically.  I have deleted and locked threads on request if it is deemed.  Both Bako and Bane have asked for locking of threads and the administrators/moderators have complied in the past.<br>
<br>
Please feel free to look into the moderator position then you can help deal with it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
